S1-pbFSxd.content:
It might seem hard to use at first but i will try to explain how it works first
Put an i2c object then write the i2c device address after that write the address you want to begin at then pulse the start to queue then use the byte and write to pulse bytes to queue
when you reach the number in {Num} it will begin writing to the i2c device
the reset input can be pulsed to reset the counter and to flush the queue so it can be used to begin writing the queue without waiting
for the expected {Num} to be reached
